In other words, aiming for a system that’s flexible, adaptable, and grounded in real-world feedback will likely be more effective than striving for a perfectly consistent theoretical framework. This approach can help you avoid the trap of pursuing an impossible ideal and focus on creating something practical and impactful.', 'direction': 'out', 'decoding_id': None}
